<HEADLINE>
SAINT LUCIA BECOMES TAIWAN'S 25TH DIPLOMATIC ALLY: PREMIER
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, April 25 (CNA) 04/26/07  11:10:02 (By Sofia Wu)
</P>
<P>
Premier Su Tseng-chang said Wednesday that Saint Lucia has become
Taiwan's 25th diplomatic ally.
</P>
<P>
Su made the remarks while attending a ceremony marking the
establishment of a supporter group in Taoyuan County's Chungli
City in northern Taiwan for his bid to represent the ruling
Democratic Progressive Party to run in the 2008 presidential
election.
</P>
<P>
Cabinet spokeswoman Chen Mei-ling confirmed later that Saint
Lucia's  foreign affairs minister  announced  in his country's
parliament this evening that Saint Lucia is resolved to forge
diplomatic ties with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"We are pleased with Saint Lucia's announcement and our foreign
ministry will handle the follow-up proceedings," Chen said.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen, Minister of Foreign Affairs James Huang will
give a background briefing for the local news media Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The East Caribbean nation first eastablished diplomatic ties with
Taiwan in in 1984 and switched diplomatic recognition to Beijing
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Premier Su said the resumption of diplomatic ties with Saint
Lucia is one of the most encouraging news events since he assumed
premiership early last year.
</P>
